casebody.data:
Third Department,

May, 1942.

(May 6, 1942.) Eva Goggin and Walter Goggin, Plaintiffs, v. Harry Kasulke and Lucy Kasulke, Defendants.

Application to be relieved from printing medical testimony on appeal denied, without costs. The plaintiff should move to settle the case before the trial judge and if relief there is denied appeal will lie from that order. Present — Hill, P. J., Crapser, Heffeman, Schenck and Foster, JJ.
